						<summary>

						<p>Slab in a field about three furlongs to the south of the Śaṅkaranārāyaṇa temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 15th Century.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged Kannaḍa record engraved in Nāgarī script refers to a gift of land the details of which, including the date, are all lost.</p>						

						</summary>
